from numpy import log       #function for removing skewness

def skew_rem(df,col):
    q = []
    for i in df[col]:
        if(i != 0):
            q.append(log(i))
        else:
            q.append(i)
    df[col] = q

def find_boundries(df,col):
    Q1=df[col].quantile(.25)
    Q3=df[col].quantile(.75)
    IQR=Q3-Q1
    lower_boundry=Q1 -1.5*IQR
    upper_boundry=Q3 +1.5*IQR
    return lower_boundry, upper_boundry
